byline.contributor: Falih Hassan contributed reporting from Tikrit.

abstract: Iraqi soldiers give little credit to United States in drive to retake Tikrit from Islamic State.
lead_paragraph: Iraqi soldiers spent weeks in a stalemate with militants before American jets went to work, but to hear some tell it, the United States deserves little credit.

headline.main: Iraq Forces, Pushing ISIS Out of Tikrit, Give Few Thanks for U.S. Airstrikes
